text:
I thought I found a gem of a hotel at $175 a night near Central Park West, La Quinta's aren't known to be fancy, but they are comfortable. This one however, left a lot to be desired. Location was great, next to Central Park to be able to walk to the park and to the MET. However, the room left a LOT to be desired. I read reviews that the rooms were small as was the elevator, and I was ok with that. I didn't need a lot of room. However, I didn't realize just HOW small the room was. With a full double bed shoved into the corner, there was just enough room for a dresser and a couple feet to walk on either side of the bed. I'm gonna guess it was 8' or 10' x 12' foot room. That was it. The bathroom was tiny too. There were minor repairs needed that I reported to the front desk staff as I left. I understand these things happen. But when I checked out my bill came to over $477 for 2 nights. I thought I reserved at $175, but the small print. They charge a $35 resort fee per night. What kind of resort amenities I paid for, I wasn't sure. There was no pool to provide excess towels, no sauna, no weight room, no special equipment to maintain outside of general hotel equipment. Their "business center" was a table in their small lobby with a computer for guest use. Resort fee for the "free" Wifi? For the "free" breakfast? The "free" use of their business center? 

On the good side, they did have a mini-food supply store in the lobby which came in handy for a quick snack or drink. The staff were very nice, the little I had come into contact with them. It seems to be a rather old building, so I can understand the small rooms. I just can't understand the 'hidden fees', the resort fee really irritated me. Just say your room was $210 and be done with it. This was the explanation: 
Total Before Taxes and Fees $350.40
Occupancy Tax 5.875% $9.82; 
City Hotel Fee $3.50 $3.50; 
Sales Tax 8.875% $14.84; 
Resort Fee $30.00 + Tax $34.43; 
Occupancy Tax 5.875% $10.76; 
Sales Tax 8.875% $16.26. 

I upped my rating from poor to average. I just want folks to know what they are getting when they book. LOOK FOR HIDDEN CHARGES! I know New York is expensive, but this was outrageous.
